parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear subframe can cause the differential mount to become disconnected from the frame, leading to a loss of control and potentially resulting in an accident.
symptoms: the floor pan is separating from the subframe
the differential mount is becoming disconnected from the frame
visual inspections show separation of the subframe from the frame
cracking along multiple body seams in the engine compartment and rear subframe area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Differential Mount Cracking and Subframe Separation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the rear differential mount and separation of the subframe from the trunk floor can lead to unpredictable handling, especially during regular driving turns and highway speeds, causing instability, rough shaking, and loose chassis knocking, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: especially during regular driving turns and highway speeds
trunk being torn out by subframe
subframe separating from the floor of the trunk.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Subframe Separation from Vehicle Body
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the rear subframe from the vehicle body can cause unstable and unsafe handling, increasing the risk of accidents and loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit uneven or unstable handling
and may produce unusual noises or vibrations. In some cases
the separation may be visible upon inspection.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Broken Spot Welds Underneath the Vehicle
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken spot welds can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual noises or vibrations
the broken welds may be visible upon inspection.
